data.description: Here's your new, fabulous 2 story single family home in the desired Harvey Park neighborhood! The home has a large lot waiting for you to put your own personal touches in the back yard! There is a sprinkler system for the lawn, and a shed in backyard. The dining room has charming and original hardwood floors along with coffered ceiling and bay window for additional sunlight. The dining area is a main point as it leads you to the living room, kitchen and hallway to bedrooms. The living room contains both traditional windows and sky lights for brilliant sunshine in your living space. Note that this space is in an L-shape, providing enough separation to create a reading nook, play or work area for a successful multi-use living space! The open kitchen features charming tile countertops, pine cabinetry, fan and light combo overhead, and the first access to the backyard perfect for a summer cookout! The kitchen also sits adjacent to an oversized laundry and pantry combo with a secondary access door to the backyard. Down the hall, you’ll find the primary, secondary bedroom, and main level bathroom. Head upstairs where you’ll find a a third and fourth bedroom large enough to use as office, gym, play area, or guest bedroom(s). The upstairs bathroom was recently remodeled, featuring a tiled standing shower, newer light fixtures, and a vanity. AC replaced within the last two years! The home also has newly refinished, solid hardwood floors, newly painted interior + exterior, new baseboard trim, and mulch in front yard.The neighborhood is conveniently located; Just blocks to Federal for a quick trip on 285 and/or i-25! Shops, both Ruby Hill Park & the Bear Creek Greenbelt, restaurants, both College View & Harvey Park Rec Centers, elementary to high schools, are all within a 3 mile radius to the home. Downtown Denver is a short 18 min commute, & you’re 20 minutes to DTC. There's so much this home and community offer-Book your tour now!
